name: Mad Takes Off on Vacations and Other Threats to Our National Security
Horror Sci-Fi ... and Other Weird Things
Mad Nick at Nite Viewer's Companion

description: Classic, genre-bending spoofs, including the classic parody of Tarzan, "Melvin!" Plus art by Jack Davis, John Severin, Al Feldstein, Wally Wood and Will Elder!
Featuring the classic satires "Dragged Net!" and "The Lone Stranger"--plus vampires!
Featuring the classic spoof (and MAD's first ever superhero parody!) "Superduperman"! Plus spoofs of Robin Hood, The Shadow and more!
Featuring the spoof of the Blackhawk comic book! Plus parodies of private eye and horror comics--and much more!
Featuring a satire of "Terry and the Pirates" a second installment of "Melvin of the Apes!", a poetry spoof of "Casey at the Bat" and MAD's classic King Kong parody, "Ping Pong!"

Including MAD's classic spoofs of Sherlock Holmes and Treasure Island plus Harvey Kurtzman's "Hey Look!" and more!

  • Melvin Can't Find Mad / Subscription Ad ( Will Elder art)
  • Shermlock Shomes! ( Will Elder art)
  • Treasure Island! ( John Severin art)
  • Operation Under The Ground (chapter 1)
  • Mad Mumblings
  • Hey Look! ( Harvey Kurtzman early creations)
  • Smilin' Melvin! ( Wally Wood art)
Containing MAD's classic spoofs, "Bat Boy and Rubin!", "Frank N. Stein!", "The Lone Stranger Rides Again!", and Harvey Kurtzman's "Hey Look!"
Featuring the classic parody "Little Orphan Melvin!", the poetry spoof of "The Raven", a movie parody of High Noon and more!
Featuring the classic, Wally Wood-illustrated "Sound Effects!", the Jack Davis-drawn "Paul Revere's Ride!" and MAD's spoof of "The Katzenjammer Kids"--plus more!
Featuring MAD's classic spoofs of comic book ads, "Popeye" and On the Waterfront -- plus the Jack Davis-illustrated "Slow Motion!" and more! With art by Will Elder and Wally Wood!
MAD's legendary "Art Issue"--with a classic series of Will Elder-illustrated articles following one man's artistic progression from "The Child!" to "Senility!"

Featuring classic spoofs of "Pogo," "Ripley's Believe It or Not!" and The Barefoot Contessa--plus the Jack Davis-illustrated "Scenes We'd...Like to See!" With art by Johnny Craig, Jack Kamen and Wally Wood!
